And now (my Parents) tho I cannot caſt your natural bread, yer I truſt I am full of the bread of life, and ſhall be ſo for evermore. There is a fulneſs of fat things in the houſe not made with hands, in Heaven; There God and Chriſt ſit on the Throne, and the Saints ſhall; 
                  〈◊〉
                where too, for they ſhall judg the world. O that we would judg our ſelves now.
